FBIS4-11733 "drnes063_s_94011" FBIS-NES-94-063 Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 SOUTH ASIA Iran Transfer of Space Technology to Developing Countries Urged Transfer of Space Technology to Developing Countries Urged LD3103193794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in English 1130 GMT 31 Mar 94 LD3103193794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran English BFN [Text] The Islamic Republic of Iran calls for international cooperation for transfer of space technology to the developing countries. Islamic Republic of Iran's representative mentioned the point in the 33rd session of the Legal Subcommittee for Peaceful Use of Outer Space saying the space technology should be put at the disposal of larger number of countries and people in the world. The Iranian representative said outer space should be allocated to peaceful activities based on the UN ratifications. The Iranian representative has mentioned the space technology as a helpful means for promotion of communication for protection of the living environment and predictions of natural incidents, calling on the UN to make efforts to attain the objective through creating regional mechanisms. The Legal Subcommittee of Peaceful use of outer space includes 53 members with the Islamic Republic of Iran being one of them.
